message: /* Background */ Unless Walker has the genealogical studies to identify indifvidual ancestors from 500 years ago this is not from a reliable source.
/* Background */ The claim that Jackie Walker's father was Ashkenazic is either original research or lacks a reliable source. Jackie Walker is not a reliable source.
Jackie Walker is not Jewish. Neither was she born Jewish or raised Jewish. Neither did she convert to Judaism. Her father was Jewish. Having a Jewish father doesn't make you Jewish.

Undid revision 868788742 by [[Special:Contributions/RevertBob|RevertBob]] ([[User talk:RevertBob|talk]]) Readding content fully supported by RS and removing original research, eg the claim that Jackie Walker's mother was a Sephardic Jew or descended from Sephardic Jews. Jackie Walker's own claims about her ancestry are not RS. No RS has ever said that Jackie Walker's mom was a Jew or descended from Jews. The claim that Walker's dad was Ashkenazic is also unsupported.
It was extremely rare for persons abducted as slaves from Africa to be of purely Christian or Jewish descent.
The slaves who were abducted from Africa were rarely if ever Christians.

/* Background */ There is no reason to link to an article on Ashkenazic Jews, since there is no evidence that her father was Ashkenazic, Sephardic, both or neither. The name Cohen is common among all Jews.
/* Background */ Added native African religious descent since the victims of slavery were generally not Christian when the slavers abducted them.
/* Background */ Jackie Walker didn't claim her mother was merely of partial Jewish ancestry, so I removed this word.
Clarified a poorly worded point that I made.
/* Jewish */  I agreed with Bangalamania that Wikipedia should not state that Jackie Walker is Jewish.
/* Personal life */ It has not been established that Walker is Jewish, merely that she has a Jewish father.
/* Background */ Although Walker may have stated that her mother was Jewish that has not been shown to be a fact.
/* Background */ It has not been established that her father was either Sephardic, Mizrahi or both. Cohen is a common name among all Jews. Some Soviet Jews were Sephardic.
Her Jamaican ancestors on her mother's side included Christians, so adding that fact is pertinent.
/* Plot */ The people who shoot themselves immediately upon news of the surrender are not identified as soldiers or civilians.
/* Plot */ Gunshots indicate suicide but there is no indication whether those killing themselves are officers or not.
/* Plot */ Hitler in the film reacts calmly to Speer's disobedience.
/* Plot */ When the message from Goering arrives Hitler orders his arrest but not his execution.
/* Plot */ Unlike the other major characters in the film, Peter Kranz was fictional and did not exist in real life.
/* Plot */ Hitler tells Fegelein, Speer and others that in one of the next scenes following the scene with Himmler.

/* Plot */ In the film, Himmler tells Fegelein that he intends to negotiate with the Allies. Fegelein asks why the Allies would negotiate with him and warns that any attempt to do so is treason. Fegelein does not reiterate Himmler's thoughts on negotiations but rather expresses mild disagreement with it.
/* Plot */ Himmler does not leave Berlin secretly in the film. Only his attempts to negotiate with the Allies is secret.

The film does not end with Hitler's death but continues to show the secretary Traudl Junge and others attempting to flee Berlin. Junge's book was not based on multiple sources but was simply her own recollection of her years with Adolf Hitler and her attempted escape from Hitler's bunker in 1945.

/* Development */ Mohnke and Schenk were SS officers and were depicted as such in the film. This information is relevant because SS officers routinely killed prisoners and conducted medical experiments on concentration camp inmates.
Fantastic is more consistent with normal English usage.
/* Events in 1945 */ That is an opinion
Made the reference to the week Hitler died more specific by giving the exact date. Made the reference prefaced "shortly before" more specific by giving the exact day.
Heidegger was a member of the Nazi Party for 12 years 1933-1945 and not simply in 1934.
